567
00:55:39,391 --> 00:55:40,851
- So I ran away.

568
00:55:42,656 --> 00:55:44,157
What about your mom, then?

569
00:55:44,658 --> 00:55:47,744
I love my mom very much!

570
00:55:48,213 --> 00:55:50,132
- But she can be very scary.

571
00:55:50,152 --> 00:55:52,071
- Just like my mom.

572
00:55:57,254 --> 00:55:58,546
Ponyo, over here, please.

573
00:56:15,147 --> 00:56:17,857
I wonder if the fuel has gone bad.

574
00:56:18,452 --> 00:56:19,704
- Maybe it's clogged.

575
00:56:19,724 --> 00:56:20,976
- It's clogged.

576
00:56:21,069 --> 00:56:22,904
It's clogged over there.

577
00:56:38,555 --> 00:56:39,911
- It's on!

578
00:56:39,931 --> 00:56:41,287
- It's light now!

579
00:56:43,634 --> 00:56:45,092
Ponyo, you're amazing.

580
00:57:03,413 --> 00:57:04,811
- Antenna, antenna!

581
00:57:04,831 --> 00:57:06,229
- Hey, Lisa.

582
00:57:06,323 --> 00:57:08,366
Did all the ships out there sink?

583
00:57:09,743 --> 00:57:11,494
I don't see any lights out there.

584
00:57:29,815 --> 00:57:31,254
- Too loud!

585
00:57:31,274 --> 00:57:32,713
- We can't get through?

586
00:57:33,976 --> 00:57:36,435
I can't get any reception.

587
00:57:37,573 --> 00:57:39,659
Transmitting from JA4LL.

588
00:57:39,679 --> 00:57:41,765
JA4LL.

589
00:57:42,109 --> 00:57:43,401
Come in, Koichi.

590
00:57:44,069 --> 00:57:46,362
This is Lisa, Sosuke and Ponyo.

591
00:57:46,697 --> 00:57:48,406
We're all doing fine.

592
00:57:49,710 --> 00:57:51,754
- We're about to have dinner.

593
00:57:51,774 --> 00:57:53,818
- Ham!

594
00:58:02,431 --> 00:58:03,453
Put the noodles in your bowl?

595
00:58:03,473 --> 00:58:04,495
Be careful.

596
00:58:04,515 --> 00:58:05,537
It's really hot.

597
00:58:21,867 --> 00:58:23,514
- You have to wait a little bit.

598
00:58:23,534 --> 00:58:25,181
- It takes three minutes.

599
00:58:40,417 --> 00:58:41,834
OK, close your eyes.

600
00:58:43,045 --> 00:58:44,295
Not yet...

601
00:58:47,100 --> 00:58:47,997
Ponyo...

602
00:58:48,017 --> 00:58:48,914
No peeking!

603
00:58:52,648 --> 00:58:53,524
OK.

604
00:58:53,544 --> 00:58:54,420
You can look now.

605
00:58:55,390 --> 00:58:57,683
Abracadabra!

606
00:59:03,992 --> 00:59:05,307
- It's ham!

607
00:59:05,327 --> 00:59:06,642
- Careful, it's hot.

608
00:59:08,195 --> 00:59:10,863
Hot, hot, hot!

609
00:59:28,215 --> 00:59:29,966
Lisa, Ponyo fell asleep.

610
00:59:37,349 --> 00:59:39,850
Do you think Ponyo came from far, far away?

611
00:59:39,935 --> 00:59:41,602
Yeah, I do.

612
00:59:57,462 --> 00:59:58,797
Look outside.

613
00:59:58,817 --> 01:00:00,152
It looks like the waves have calmed down.

614
01:00:01,508 --> 01:00:03,051
- Maybe because Ponyo fell asleep.

615
01:00:03,071 --> 01:00:04,614
- Do you see that light?

616
01:00:12,436 --> 01:00:13,917
It's moving.

617
01:00:13,937 --> 01:00:15,418
There must be somebody still over there.

618
01:00:15,512 --> 01:00:17,513
I wonder if that's Yoshie and the others.

619
01:00:24,114 --> 01:00:25,366
- The lights are out.

620
01:00:25,386 --> 01:00:26,638
- It's the mountain road.

621
01:00:30,777 --> 01:00:32,695
Sosuke, stay with Ponyo, OK?

622
01:00:44,207 --> 01:00:45,458
I've gotta go help them.

623
01:00:45,542 --> 01:00:47,668
I can get there if I take the mountain road.

624
01:00:51,048 --> 01:00:53,466
Sosuke, I should go to the senior center.

625
01:00:53,675 --> 01:00:54,842
I'm coming, too.

626
01:00:55,719 --> 01:00:58,095
I'd feel better if you'd stay up here with Ponyo.

627
01:00:58,398 --> 01:01:00,025
I'm coming with you!

628
01:01:00,045 --> 01:01:01,672
We just need to bring Ponyo with us.

629
01:01:02,184 --> 01:01:03,476
I wanna go with you, Lisa!

630
01:01:06,104 --> 01:01:09,940
Sosuke, right now, our house is a beacon in the storm.

631
01:01:10,025 --> 01:01:14,153
The people in the dark feel hopeful when they see our lights.

632
01:01:14,237 --> 01:01:16,113
That's why someone has to be here.

633
01:01:17,115 --> 01:01:19,283
Many mysterious things have been happening.

634
01:01:19,367 --> 01:01:23,621
We don't know why right now, but we'll find out before long.

635
01:01:23,705 --> 01:01:26,874
For now, I'm worried about the people at the senior center.

636
01:01:26,958 --> 01:01:31,337
If you stay and guard the house, that would be very helpful.

637
01:01:31,431 --> 01:01:32,912
Don't worry.

638
01:01:32,932 --> 01:01:34,413
I promise I'll be back.

639
01:01:35,717 --> 01:01:37,426
Promise?

640
01:01:38,522 --> 01:01:40,003
- I promise.

641
01:01:40,023 --> 01:01:41,504
- You promised.

642
01:01:42,265 --> 01:01:43,933
I love you, Sosuke.

643
01:02:38,665 --> 01:02:40,230
The moon is out!

644
01:02:40,250 --> 01:02:41,815
I can see the lights of a city up ahead.

645
01:02:42,294 --> 01:02:43,754
Thank goodness!

646
01:02:43,774 --> 01:02:45,234
We can get our bearings again.

647
01:02:45,620 --> 01:02:47,663
We're someplace I've never seen before.

648
01:02:53,753 --> 01:02:56,630
Have we arrived in America or what?

649
01:03:14,201 --> 01:03:16,036
That's not a mountain.

650
01:03:16,056 --> 01:03:17,891
And that's no harbor, either.

651
01:03:17,986 --> 01:03:19,361
Those lights are ships.

652
01:03:29,289 --> 01:03:32,208
The water of the ocean has come together to create a mountain.

653
01:03:32,918 --> 01:03:34,919
That's probably a graveyard for ships.

654
01:03:35,003 --> 01:03:37,254
The gate to the world beyond must have opened!

655
01:03:42,395 --> 01:03:43,897
- The engine stopped!

656
01:03:43,917 --> 01:03:45,419
- Try to hold her steady.

657
01:03:45,523 --> 01:03:46,587
- Drop the sea anchor.

658
01:03:46,607 --> 01:03:47,671
- Yes, sir.

659
01:04:01,488 --> 01:04:03,280
Something's coming from behind us.

660
01:04:31,268 --> 01:04:32,851
I just saw the Goddess of Mercy!

661
01:04:43,373 --> 01:04:44,666
- The engine's working.

662
01:04:44,686 --> 01:04:45,979
- We're saved!

663
01:04:46,084 --> 01:04:47,649
She saved us!

664
01:04:47,669 --> 01:04:49,234
She must've appeared for us!

665
01:04:49,327 --> 01:04:52,871
Thank you for protecting us...

666
01:05:20,150 --> 01:05:21,525
Higher, higher.

667
01:05:35,248 --> 01:05:37,750
There is a powerful holy barrier around the house.

668
01:05:37,834 --> 01:05:40,169
How has she learned to do something like that?

669
01:05:57,864 --> 01:05:59,386
I don't believe this!

670
01:05:59,406 --> 01:06:00,928
She's turned into a human!

671
01:06:01,159 --> 01:06:02,334
Hold still!

672
01:06:02,354 --> 01:06:03,529
You...

673
01:06:03,549 --> 01:06:04,724
What are you doing?

674
01:06:12,796 --> 01:06:14,110
Girls!

675
01:06:14,130 --> 01:06:15,444
Oh, no!

676
01:06:18,666 --> 01:06:19,833
Stop, now!

677
01:06:27,644 --> 01:06:29,083
Listen, girls.

678
01:06:29,103 --> 01:06:30,542
I'm concerned about your sister.

679
01:06:36,393 --> 01:06:39,395
At last, she has finally come.

680
01:07:16,192 --> 01:07:17,735
- Fujimoto.

681
01:07:17,755 --> 01:07:19,298
- You've come for me, my love.

682
01:07:20,603 --> 01:07:22,146
What a wonderful ocean.

683
01:07:26,327 --> 01:07:28,809
It's full of magic and power.

684
01:07:28,829 --> 01:07:31,311
It's like my ancient Devonian Sea.

685
01:07:31,823 --> 01:07:33,824
Ponyo has tasted human blood.

686
01:07:34,159 --> 01:07:37,453
She also drank all of my elixirs that I've collected.

687
01:07:38,298 --> 01:07:39,966
Ponyo?

688
01:07:39,986 --> 01:07:41,654
What a lovely name.

689
01:07:47,589 --> 01:07:49,423
Of course, it's all my fault, really.

690
01:07:50,008 --> 01:07:54,470
She can use magic freely, and she's opened a hole in the fabric of reality.

691
01:07:54,554 --> 01:07:57,222
She has no idea what she's doing.

692
01:07:57,442 --> 01:08:00,195
She's now a little girl.

693
01:08:00,215 --> 01:08:02,968
And she loves a little boy.

694
01:08:03,813 --> 01:08:07,107
If we don't do anything about this, the planet is doomed.

695
01:08:16,284 --> 01:08:19,244
Already the Earth is pulling satellites from the sky.

696
01:08:19,329 --> 01:08:21,788
And the moon pulls the sea closer...

697
01:08:22,790 --> 01:08:24,208
Be calm, dear.

698
01:08:31,976 --> 01:08:34,062
Sosuke.

699
01:08:34,082 --> 01:08:36,168
The boy's name is Sosuke.

700
01:08:39,390 --> 01:08:43,352
You all love your older sister, don't you?

701
01:08:46,648 --> 01:08:49,983
Listen, my darling, why don't we let Ponyo become human for good?

702
01:08:50,078 --> 01:08:51,225
- What?

703
01:08:51,245 --> 01:08:52,392
- It's the old magic, you know.

704
01:08:53,071 --> 01:08:57,866
If Sosuke's love remains unchanged, Ponyo'll become human and lose her magical power.

705
01:08:57,951 --> 01:09:02,579
But, if anything goes wrong, Ponyo will turn into sea foam.

706
01:09:03,081 --> 01:09:06,625
Well, we all originated in sea foam.

707
01:09:06,719 --> 01:09:08,159
But he is only five years old.

708
01:09:08,179 --> 01:09:09,619
That's impossible...

709
01:09:15,134 --> 01:09:18,345
Children, sleep peacefully for now.

710
01:09:31,818 --> 01:09:35,904
Sosuke!

711
01:09:36,990 --> 01:09:38,031
Ponyo, you OK?

712
01:09:41,170 --> 01:09:43,277
- Ponyo, good morning.

713
01:09:43,297 --> 01:09:45,404
- Good morning, Sosuke.

714
01:09:51,806 --> 01:09:52,849
Look at that.

715
01:09:52,869 --> 01:09:53,912
The ocean is at our door.

716
01:10:17,790 --> 01:10:19,813
- How come your Lisa's not here?

717
01:10:19,833 --> 01:10:21,856
- Because the road is under the water.

718
01:10:21,951 --> 01:10:24,369
Too bad we don't have a boat.

719
01:10:27,957 --> 01:10:29,458
There's a boat, right there!

720
01:10:31,763 --> 01:10:32,952
- You can't ride it.

721
01:10:32,972 --> 01:10:34,161
- Yes, you can.

722
01:10:50,480 --> 01:10:51,688
Thank you!

723
01:10:53,576 --> 01:10:55,036
Wow!

724
01:10:55,056 --> 01:10:56,516
You even made the candle bigger.

725
01:10:56,621 --> 01:10:57,546
- We can ride it!

726
01:10:57,566 --> 01:10:58,491
- Yeah!

727
01:10:58,511 --> 01:10:59,436
This is fantastic.

728
01:10:59,540 --> 01:11:00,833
- Fantastic!

729
01:11:00,853 --> 01:11:02,146
- You take that end, please.

730
01:11:02,241 --> 01:11:03,241
OK!

731
01:11:06,005 --> 01:11:07,257
- Ready?

732
01:11:07,277 --> 01:11:08,529
- I'm ready!

733
01:11:21,678 --> 01:11:22,928
It actually floats!

734
01:11:25,682 --> 01:11:27,933
Doesn't look like it has any leaks.

735
01:11:28,361 --> 01:11:30,780
Now we have to fill the boiler.

736
01:11:30,800 --> 01:11:33,219
The water goes in through this pipe...

737
01:11:34,190 --> 01:11:36,733
...then it gets heated up here, in this round thing.

738
01:12:04,178 --> 01:12:05,846
It's like a rocket.

739
01:12:13,062 --> 01:12:14,813
Ponyo, everything's shipshape.

740
01:12:14,907 --> 01:12:15,783
- Shipshape!

741
01:12:15,803 --> 01:12:16,679
- Yep.

742
01:12:16,784 --> 01:12:17,952
- Shipshape!

743
01:12:17,972 --> 01:12:19,140
- Shipshape.

744
01:12:19,245 --> 01:12:20,080
Shipshape!

745
01:12:20,100 --> 01:12:20,935
Shipshape!

746
01:12:20,955 --> 01:12:21,790
Shipshape!

747
01:12:21,810 --> 01:12:22,645
Shipshape!

748
01:12:22,739 --> 01:12:23,739
Shipshape!

749
01:12:45,104 --> 01:12:46,106
Is it hot?

750
01:12:46,126 --> 01:12:47,128
It's hot!

751
01:12:52,351 --> 01:12:53,435
Hot!

752
01:12:57,158 --> 01:12:58,472
- Look at that!

753
01:12:58,492 --> 01:12:59,806
- It's burning.

754
01:12:59,911 --> 01:13:00,662
It's hot!

755
01:13:00,682 --> 01:13:01,433
It's hot!

756
01:13:01,453 --> 01:13:02,204
It's hot!

757
01:13:02,224 --> 01:13:02,975
It's hot!

758
01:13:10,995 --> 01:13:12,621
It's hot, right?

759
01:13:23,633 --> 01:13:24,966
It's working!

760
01:13:26,803 --> 01:13:29,429
Sosuke, we're shipshape, right?

761
01:13:29,524 --> 01:13:30,463
- Yep.

762
01:13:30,483 --> 01:13:31,422
- This is fantastic.

763
01:13:39,200 --> 01:13:40,056
- Sosuke!

764
01:13:40,076 --> 01:13:40,932
We're happy, right?

765
01:13:40,952 --> 01:13:41,808
- Yep.

766
01:13:42,370 --> 01:13:43,747
- Sosuke, it's burning, right?

767
01:13:43,767 --> 01:13:45,144
- Yep.

768
01:13:45,655 --> 01:13:47,739
Sosuke, that thing is hot, right?

769
01:13:48,543 --> 01:13:50,358
Ponyo, you be the boat's lookout.

770
01:13:50,378 --> 01:13:52,193
And I'll do the steering, OK?

771
01:13:52,755 --> 01:13:53,590
OK!

772
01:13:53,610 --> 01:13:54,445
I'm the lookout!

773
01:14:21,524 --> 01:14:22,774
There's the road.

774
01:14:22,859 --> 01:14:25,193
That's the mountain road Lisa took last night.

775
01:14:27,707 --> 01:14:29,104
- I don't see her anywhere.

776
01:14:29,124 --> 01:14:30,521
- We'll see her.

777
01:14:30,950 --> 01:14:32,993
She promised me she'd come back.

778
01:14:37,884 --> 01:14:39,552
Those are ancient fish.

779
01:14:39,572 --> 01:14:41,240
They lived during the Devonian Age.

780
01:14:41,345 --> 01:14:42,680
I know that one.

781
01:14:42,700 --> 01:14:44,035
It's Bothriocephalus.

782
01:14:48,644 --> 01:14:49,833
- And that one is...

783
01:14:49,853 --> 01:14:51,042
- Dipnorhynchus.

784
01:14:51,147 --> 01:14:52,475
- Dipnorhynchus!

785
01:14:52,495 --> 01:14:53,823
- Wow!

786
01:14:53,843 --> 01:14:55,171
That one's really huge!

787
01:14:55,276 --> 01:14:56,694
- That's Devonynchus!

788
01:14:56,714 --> 01:14:58,132
- Devonynchus!

789
01:15:05,359 --> 01:15:10,155
Ahoy!

790
01:15:10,249 --> 01:15:11,209
- Ahoy...

791
01:15:11,229 --> 01:15:12,189
- Whoa, there's a boat!

792
01:15:13,284 --> 01:15:14,910
Ahoy!

793
01:15:16,245 --> 01:15:17,579
They said, "Ahoy."

794
01:15:18,998 --> 01:15:20,916
Ahoy!

795
01:15:26,797 --> 01:15:27,881
That's fast!

796
01:15:31,177 --> 01:15:32,594
I'm getting the hang of this.

797
01:15:36,265 --> 01:15:37,933
Get ready to stop, Ponyo.

798
01:15:44,200 --> 01:15:45,222
- Hello, you two.

799
01:15:45,242 --> 01:15:46,264
- Hello.

800
01:15:46,359 --> 01:15:48,902
Hey, that is quite a boat you got there.

801
01:15:49,330 --> 01:15:50,811
I've seen you before.

802
01:15:50,831 --> 01:15:52,312
You're Lisa's little boy, aren't you?

803
01:15:52,625 --> 01:15:53,842
- He's not a little boy.

804
01:15:53,862 --> 01:15:55,079
He's Sosuke!

805
01:15:55,099 --> 01:15:56,316
- She's Ponyo.

806
01:15:57,787 --> 01:15:59,955
And I used to be a fish.

807
01:16:00,331 --> 01:16:01,623
A fish?

808
01:16:02,583 --> 01:16:04,459
Your name is lovely, Ponyo.

809
01:16:06,796 --> 01:16:08,838
By the way, have you seen my mother?

810
01:16:08,933 --> 01:16:10,685
Your mother?

811
01:16:10,705 --> 01:16:12,457
Why isn't your mother with you?

812
01:16:12,979 --> 01:16:14,397
- She went to the senior center.

813
01:16:14,417 --> 01:16:15,835
- Wow, way up there?

814
01:16:15,930 --> 01:16:17,472
This is our baby.

815
01:16:47,513 --> 01:16:48,493
Oh, dear.

816
01:16:48,513 --> 01:16:49,493
I wonder what's wrong.

817
01:16:55,845 --> 01:16:57,846
Oh, is that for us?

818
01:17:11,527 --> 01:17:13,028
Let me have it.

819
01:17:18,002 --> 01:17:19,649
Thank you.

820
01:17:19,669 --> 01:17:21,316
I'm looking forward to tasting it.

821
01:17:24,749 --> 01:17:27,083
Wow, that's good soup.

822
01:17:27,720 --> 01:17:29,513
- My mom made it.

823
01:17:29,533 --> 01:17:31,326
- The soup's for the baby!

824
01:17:32,131 --> 01:17:34,090
Oh, I'm sorry.

825
01:17:34,185 --> 01:17:37,772
He's too young to have soup.

826
01:17:37,792 --> 01:17:41,379
But I could eat the soup instead, and it would help me make milk for him.

827
01:17:43,601 --> 01:17:45,894
Yeah, my mom made milk for me, too.

828
01:17:46,479 --> 01:17:49,731
Ponyo, is it all right if I eat the soup?

829
01:17:49,825 --> 01:17:51,432
- That's fine.

830
01:17:51,452 --> 01:17:53,059
- Thank you.

831
01:17:54,361 --> 01:17:55,862
Heave-ho!

832
01:17:57,124 --> 01:17:59,043
Heave-ho!

833
01:17:59,063 --> 01:18:00,982
Heave-ho!

834
01:18:02,828 --> 01:18:04,329
Heave-ho!

835
01:18:10,971 --> 01:18:12,681
People from the town!

836
01:18:12,701 --> 01:18:14,411
It's just like a parade!

837
01:18:14,809 --> 01:18:17,082
Ahoy!

838
01:18:17,102 --> 01:18:19,375
Are any of you in need of assistance at this time?

839
01:18:19,772 --> 01:18:22,170
Thank you!

840
01:18:22,190 --> 01:18:24,588
We're fine for now!

841
01:18:25,101 --> 01:18:27,936
We are taking everyone to the Mountain Peak Hotel!

842
01:18:28,020 --> 01:18:30,730
For your safety, we request that you follow us!

843
01:18:30,825 --> 01:18:31,952
Aye, aye!

844
01:18:31,972 --> 01:18:33,099
Will do!

845
01:18:35,412 --> 01:18:36,789
- Looks like the whole town is here.

846
01:18:36,809 --> 01:18:38,186
- I'm glad.

847
01:18:38,290 --> 01:18:39,750
- I hope everyone's OK.

848
01:18:39,770 --> 01:18:41,230
- Ponyo, time to light the candle.

849
01:18:41,335 --> 01:18:42,315
Hold on a second.

850
01:18:42,335 --> 01:18:43,315
Let's see...

851
01:18:49,083 --> 01:18:50,416
Here, have some milk.

852
01:18:51,001 --> 01:18:52,001
Wow.

853
01:18:53,462 --> 01:18:54,546
It's for milk.

854
01:18:54,630 --> 01:18:57,173
She already ate all the ham off those sandwiches.

855
01:18:57,268 --> 01:18:58,790
Thank you.

856
01:18:58,810 --> 01:19:00,332
It'll help me make good milk.

857
01:19:00,427 --> 01:19:01,427
Sosuke.

858
01:19:02,106 --> 01:19:03,389
- I have a used candle.

859
01:19:03,409 --> 01:19:04,692
Do you want it?

860
01:19:04,712 --> 01:19:05,995
- Thanks.

861
01:19:06,015 --> 01:19:07,298
Ponyo will make it bigger.

862
01:19:07,393 --> 01:19:08,393
Thank you!

863
01:19:09,238 --> 01:19:10,177
- Be careful.

864
01:19:10,197 --> 01:19:11,136
- Thank you.

865
01:19:17,820 --> 01:19:18,945
What's the matter?

866
01:19:23,878 --> 01:19:24,358
There.

867
01:19:24,378 --> 01:19:24,858
There.

868
01:19:44,513 --> 01:19:45,722
Ponyo!

869
01:19:58,996 --> 01:20:00,331
- Sosuke!

870
01:20:00,351 --> 01:20:01,686
- Hey, that's Sosuke.

871
01:20:02,499 --> 01:20:03,855
- Where is Lisa?

872
01:20:03,875 --> 01:20:05,231
- What's going on with Lisa?

873
01:20:05,336 --> 01:20:07,004
She went to the senior center last night!

874
01:20:07,024 --> 01:20:08,692
We're on our way to find her!

875
01:20:08,787 --> 01:20:11,998
That means Lisa beat that wave!

876
01:20:12,092 --> 01:20:13,636
- That's Lisa.

877
01:20:13,656 --> 01:20:15,200
- Sosuke, can I ride with you?

878
01:20:15,888 --> 01:20:17,223
Kumiko, I'm busy right now.

879
01:20:17,243 --> 01:20:18,578
Maybe later.

880
01:20:18,682 --> 01:20:20,476
Check the park.

881
01:20:20,496 --> 01:20:22,290
The seniors should be there by now.

882
01:20:22,394 --> 01:20:23,500
- Good luck, kid!

883
01:20:23,520 --> 01:20:24,626
- You'll find her!

884
01:20:24,720 --> 01:20:29,265
We'll send a boat for the seniors as soon as we drop this group off!

885
01:20:29,350 --> 01:20:31,226
Good luck, captain!

886
01:21:20,192 --> 01:21:22,944
Ponyo, we need to replace the candle.

887
01:21:26,792 --> 01:21:28,357
We'll be OK.

888
01:21:28,377 --> 01:21:29,942
The fisherman gave me another one.

889
01:21:30,995 --> 01:21:31,995
Hot!

890
01:21:32,413 --> 01:21:33,788
It's still pretty hot.

891
01:21:38,961 --> 01:21:41,170
Bye-bye.

892
01:21:42,516 --> 01:21:44,059
Here, Ponyo.

893
01:21:44,079 --> 01:21:45,622
Can you make this bigger?

894
01:21:46,051 --> 01:21:47,176
All right.

895
01:21:53,142 --> 01:21:55,977
Ponyo, are you sleepy?

896
01:22:03,068 --> 01:22:04,110
Ponyo.

897
01:22:20,304 --> 01:22:21,139
Ponyo.

898
01:22:21,159 --> 01:22:21,994
Ponyo!

899
01:23:19,780 --> 01:23:20,885
Oh, good.

900
01:23:20,905 --> 01:23:22,010
I can walk from here.

901
01:23:48,882 --> 01:23:50,091
There's the road.

902
01:24:02,990 --> 01:24:03,532
Oh, no!

903
01:24:03,552 --> 01:24:04,094
The boat!

904
01:24:05,899 --> 01:24:27,962
Ponyo!

905
01:24:29,131 --> 01:24:31,174
Ponyo, wake up!

906
01:24:33,635 --> 01:24:35,094
Sosuke.

907
01:24:41,560 --> 01:24:43,144
You scared me.

908
01:24:43,228 --> 01:24:45,813
I thought you might turn back into a goldfish.

909
01:24:58,629 --> 01:25:00,256
Lisa's car!

910
01:25:00,276 --> 01:25:01,903
Ponyo, I found Lisa's car!

911
01:25:06,011 --> 01:25:07,304
Lisa!

912
01:25:07,324 --> 01:25:08,617
Lisa!

913
01:25:11,173 --> 01:25:21,349
Lisa!

914
01:25:23,101 --> 01:25:24,101
Lisa...

915
01:25:26,355 --> 01:25:27,355
Lisa.

916
01:25:30,359 --> 01:25:36,697
Lisa!

917
01:26:05,227 --> 01:26:07,603
Sosuke, I've got your boat.

918
01:26:07,688 --> 01:26:10,398
There's water coming from your eyes.

919
01:26:17,291 --> 01:26:18,751
- Let's go find your mom.

920
01:26:18,771 --> 01:26:20,231
- Yeah.

921
01:27:01,460 --> 01:27:05,443
HIMAWARI HOUSE - My lap blanket!

922
01:27:05,463 --> 01:27:09,446
- Forget about it!

923
01:27:09,541 --> 01:27:11,959
Look, here comes a whale again!

924
01:27:12,044 --> 01:27:13,753
I think he sees us.

925
01:27:13,837 --> 01:27:15,755
The other side is nice, isn't it?

926
01:27:15,849 --> 01:27:17,309
- And my knees don't hurt.

927
01:27:17,329 --> 01:27:18,789
- We didn't have to be afraid.

928
01:27:18,894 --> 01:27:20,271
This is the other side?

929
01:27:20,291 --> 01:27:21,668
I thought it was the undersea palace!

930
01:27:24,348 --> 01:27:27,475
Ladies, can we gather around, please?

931
01:27:27,569 --> 01:27:29,092
- Coming!

932
01:27:29,112 --> 01:27:30,635
- Let's go!

933
01:27:33,367 --> 01:27:34,889
- It's so nice to run.

934
01:27:34,909 --> 01:27:36,431
- Beat you there!

935
01:27:40,697 --> 01:27:41,989
Winner!

936
01:27:47,496 --> 01:27:49,246
Everyone, quiet, please.

937
01:27:50,040 --> 01:27:55,252
The time has come for you to bear witness to a sacred test of love.

938
01:27:55,347 --> 01:27:56,786
- Oh, how exciting!

939
01:27:56,806 --> 01:27:58,245
- Test of love!

940
01:27:58,340 --> 01:28:00,132
My heart is beating fast!

941
01:28:02,396 --> 01:28:04,398
Please, ladies!

942
01:28:04,418 --> 01:28:06,420
You're the witnesses to this sacred test.

943
01:28:06,515 --> 01:28:09,016
We ask everyone to be patient for a little while longer.

944
01:28:10,394 --> 01:28:14,730
Fujimoto, you won't let any harm come to Sosuke or Ponyo, will you?

945
01:28:14,825 --> 01:28:15,861
- Right.

946
01:28:15,881 --> 01:28:16,917
- Of course not!

947
01:28:16,937 --> 01:28:17,973
He's the father...

948
01:28:18,068 --> 01:28:19,151
Of course I wouldn't.

949
01:28:20,539 --> 01:28:21,916
My hope is Ponyo will stay asleep.

950
01:28:21,936 --> 01:28:23,313
Excuse me.

951
01:28:32,634 --> 01:28:35,032
- I'm sure he's nice at heart.

952
01:28:35,052 --> 01:28:37,450
- I wonder how Lisa's doing?

953
01:28:37,546 --> 01:28:42,341
She's with Ponyo's mother, and they've been talking all night and day.

954
01:28:50,402 --> 01:28:51,674
Poor Lisa.

955
01:28:51,694 --> 01:28:52,966
Must be hard on her.

956
01:28:53,061 --> 01:28:55,813
I wish we could hear what they're talking about.

957
01:28:55,907 --> 01:28:57,179
Oh, why don't we just ask.

958
01:28:57,199 --> 01:28:58,471
Lisa!

959
01:28:58,567 --> 01:29:01,902
Lisa!

960
01:29:07,367 --> 01:29:13,956
Please know that we are all cheering for Sosuke and Ponyo!

961
01:29:27,773 --> 01:29:29,025
- Lisa!

962
01:29:29,045 --> 01:29:30,297
- You must be anxious.

963
01:29:30,400 --> 01:29:31,610
Sosuke'll do just fine.

964
01:29:31,630 --> 01:29:32,840
He's a determined, young boy.

965
01:29:32,934 --> 01:29:33,934
Absolutely!

966
01:29:34,019 --> 01:29:35,394
He's such an upstanding boy.

967
01:29:36,323 --> 01:29:37,741
Thank you.

968
01:29:37,761 --> 01:29:39,179
Please be there for him.

969
01:29:39,274 --> 01:29:40,858
It's going to be fine.

970
01:29:48,617 --> 01:29:50,367
Ponyo, there's a tunnel.

971
01:29:50,911 --> 01:30:07,968
MOUNTAIN PEAK PARK AHEAD STOP I think I've been here before.

972
01:30:09,481 --> 01:30:11,274
- Ponyo?

973
01:30:11,294 --> 01:30:13,087
- Don't like this place.

974
01:30:17,155 --> 01:30:18,824
- Don't let go of my hand.

975
01:30:18,844 --> 01:30:20,513
- OK.

976
01:30:57,102 --> 01:31:27,923
Ponyo!

977
01:31:49,915 --> 01:31:51,174
Ponyo!

978
01:31:51,194 --> 01:31:52,453
Please don't die!

979
01:31:52,473 --> 01:31:53,732
Ponyo!

980
01:31:55,086 --> 01:31:56,296
Ponyo!

981
01:31:56,316 --> 01:31:57,526
Wake up, Ponyo!

982
01:31:58,705 --> 01:32:00,247
Be careful not to wake her.

983
01:32:01,426 --> 01:32:03,199
It's good to meet you, Sosuke.

984
01:32:03,219 --> 01:32:04,992
We've all been waiting for you.

985
01:32:05,096 --> 01:32:06,931
- The old ladies, your mother...

986
01:32:06,951 --> 01:32:08,786
- My mother?

987
01:32:08,892 --> 01:32:10,665
Won't you come with me and join them, Sosuke?

988
01:32:10,685 --> 01:32:12,458
Ponyo, too.

989
01:32:15,263 --> 01:32:18,182
Let Ponyo keep sleeping and we'll just sneak away.

990
01:32:18,276 --> 01:32:20,925
Sosuke!

991
01:32:20,945 --> 01:32:23,594
Sosuke, don't listen to that wacko!

992
01:32:24,147 --> 01:32:27,399
He tricked all the others into going with him!

993
01:32:27,494 --> 01:32:28,954
- Toki!

994
01:32:28,974 --> 01:32:30,434
- Nobody fools me!

995
01:32:31,237 --> 01:32:34,406
Like I said, there is so little time!

996
01:32:35,075 --> 01:32:36,784
Can't you see that?

997
01:32:36,868 --> 01:32:40,371
If the moon comes any closer, there will be no going back!

998
01:32:40,789 --> 01:32:43,791
If you're gonna lie, come up with a better one!

999
01:32:43,885 --> 01:32:45,199
- Sosuke, come to me!

1000
01:32:45,219 --> 01:32:46,533
- Humans!

1001
01:32:46,795 --> 01:32:48,712
Listen, Sosuke, please come with me!

1002
01:32:48,797 --> 01:32:50,881
You're the only one who can save the planet.

1003
01:32:50,966 --> 01:32:52,466
I don't want to use force.

1004
01:32:53,802 --> 01:32:54,927
Ponyo!

1005
01:32:57,180 --> 01:32:59,306
What a horrible thing to do to your father!

1006
01:33:06,032 --> 01:33:08,076
- Ponyo!

1007
01:33:08,096 --> 01:33:10,140
- Sosuke, come on!

1008
01:33:10,235 --> 01:33:11,777
Bring them to me!

1009
01:33:17,492 --> 01:33:18,826
You can do it!

1010
01:33:21,246 --> 01:33:22,746
Jump for it!

1011
01:34:02,287 --> 01:34:03,328
Girls!

1012
01:34:58,520 --> 01:34:59,563
- Lisa!

1013
01:34:59,583 --> 01:35:00,626
- Sosuke.

1014
01:35:00,720 --> 01:35:01,762
Ponyo!

1015
01:35:08,770 --> 01:35:10,562
Where am I?

1016
01:35:20,792 --> 01:35:22,669
- So this is Sosuke.

1017
01:35:22,689 --> 01:35:24,566
- How do you do?

1018
01:35:24,671 --> 01:35:26,173
- Are you Ponyo's mother?

1019
01:35:26,193 --> 01:35:27,695
- Yes.

1020
01:35:27,799 --> 01:35:30,239
You brought my daughter safely here.

1021
01:35:30,259 --> 01:35:32,699
Thank you.

1022
01:35:33,461 --> 01:35:34,753
Sosuke.

1023
01:35:34,838 --> 01:35:38,799
Ponyo opened a magic well because she wants very much to be human.

1024
01:35:39,801 --> 01:35:46,557
For her to become human, she needs you to accept and love her as she truly is.

1025
01:35:47,267 --> 01:35:51,478
You know that Ponyo was a fish, don't you?

1026
01:35:52,814 --> 01:35:56,608
She became half human when she licked your blood.

1027
01:35:56,703 --> 01:35:58,997
Oh, I see...

1028
01:35:59,017 --> 01:36:01,311
I cut my thumb, then Ponyo licked it and made it better.

1029
01:36:01,406 --> 01:36:03,991
So that's how she changed into a human.

1030
01:36:04,951 --> 01:36:08,620
Do you care if Ponyo is half fish and half human?

1031
01:36:09,048 --> 01:36:12,219
I love Ponyo as a fish, half-fish and fully human.

1032
01:36:12,239 --> 01:36:15,410
I love her in all forms.

1033
01:36:29,767 --> 01:36:32,060
Ponyo, come here, please.

1034
01:36:46,576 --> 01:36:51,205
Ponyo, Sosuke will be your guardian.

1035
01:36:54,000 --> 01:36:57,669
To become human, you must choose to abandon magic.

1036
01:36:57,754 --> 01:36:59,379
Can you do that?

1037
01:37:00,173 --> 01:37:01,173
Yes!

1038
01:37:10,068 --> 01:37:13,947
Kiss the bubble, when you return to land, and Ponyo will become a girl.

1039
01:37:13,967 --> 01:37:17,846
Five years old, just like you.

1040
01:37:21,110 --> 01:37:23,111
I'm happy for you, Ponyo.

1041
01:37:24,072 --> 01:37:26,615
Thank you very much, Ponyo's mother.

1042
01:37:32,622 --> 01:37:36,291
Everyone, the balance of nature is restored.

1043
01:37:39,754 --> 01:37:41,463
Way to go!

1044
01:37:47,262 --> 01:37:48,762
My Sosuke.

1045
01:38:13,288 --> 01:38:15,122
Thank you, Lisa.

1046
01:38:15,425 --> 01:38:16,843
Thank you.

1047
01:38:16,863 --> 01:38:18,281
I'll take care of her.

1048
01:38:29,647 --> 01:38:31,044
Everyone!

1049
01:38:31,064 --> 01:38:32,461
Are you all right?

1050
01:38:37,989 --> 01:38:39,415
- Wait, let me get your wheelchairs!

1051
01:38:39,435 --> 01:38:40,861
- Don't bother.

1052
01:38:40,881 --> 01:38:42,307
We like to walk.

1053
01:38:42,400 --> 01:38:44,276
Life begins again.

1054
01:38:47,822 --> 01:38:49,698
This is your ship, I believe.

1055
01:38:52,086 --> 01:38:54,297
- Thank you.

1056
01:38:54,317 --> 01:38:56,528
- Sorry for everything.

1057
01:38:56,632 --> 01:38:57,196
If you will.

1058
01:38:57,216 --> 01:38:57,780
May I?

1059
01:39:03,338 --> 01:39:05,005
Take care of Ponyo.

1060
01:39:07,759 --> 01:39:09,259
It's Koichi's ship!

1061
01:39:13,941 --> 01:39:15,686
Koichi!

1062
01:39:15,706 --> 01:39:17,451
Hi!

1063
01:39:17,471 --> 01:39:19,216
Over here!

1064
01:39:19,322 --> 01:39:21,012
It's Lisa!

1065
01:39:21,032 --> 01:39:22,722
And Sosuke's there, too!

1066
01:39:23,149 --> 01:39:24,816
Ahoy!

1067
01:39:24,901 --> 01:39:27,819
Look, Ponyo, there's Koichi's ship!

1068
01:41:12,425 --> 01:41:18,430
THE END
